title: For Sale:  AMD-65 Hungarian side folder AK-47
postcontent: Up for sale is my AMD-65 Hungarian-made AK-47. This is the tank crew version with the side folding metal stock. Â I've had this gun for about 5 years and it has mostly sat in my safe for that time, so the bore and barrel are perfect. I exclusively use CLP - if it is good enough for law enforcement it is good enough for me. I originally bought it for a compact truck gun, but I didnt like the idea of it possibly being stolen, so the safe has been its home.The rifle came from the factory built on a FEG Hungarian receiver, with a Tapco trigger that is smooth as silk, and two Tapco magazines.There are a couple of things I have done to make it more comfortable. First was the foreend. If you are familiar, the factry forearm is steel, which gets very hot if you run an extended magazine load thru the gun. The Hungarians solved this by putting a forward grip on the gun, but I replaced the factory forearm with a UTG quad rail system which not only isolates from heat but allows you to mount whatever optics or tactical equipment you want. I replaced the original forward grip with a variable-angle grip which can sit at any position that is comfortable.The original folding stock does not proved any cheek weld, so I got a cheek riser from AMD-65 tech which works perfectly. Also I installed an add-on butt pad which extends the stock slightly to provide a better length of pull.The original iron sights are still on the rifle, but I installed a Sightmark QD Ultra Shot reflex red dot optic, with a quick release Weaver mount This optic has has an ultra wide field of view, and multi-reticle variable brightness. It is a perfect optic for this gun - accurate with quick acquisitin.Â I also have around 200 rounds of ammo that I wont need if I sell the gun. This is not a CAI rifle. I am told that all available supply of teh AMD-65 is going to the Afghan police and these guns are only rarely available in the US. If you are intersted in a tough, accurate, and reliable compact weapon this is the gun for you.No low-ballers, please. I'm in no rush to sell. Also I travel quite a bit for work, so it may be a few days before I can answer an email.I'm in N. Florida and would prefer a FTF transaction with a FL CW permit. If you are out of state, I will want proof that you are legal to own this gun in your state.
